        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 11:41PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1141 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Farnsworth, or 13 miles northwest of Perryton, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elmwood, Perryton, Bryans Corner, Balko, and Farnsworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 AM CDT for the Panhandle
of Oklahoma...and the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
